2010-2018-part-a-wic-redemptions-by-vend.Description:
The table '2010-2018-part-a-wic-redemptions-by-vendor-county-with-family-counts' contains data on the number of redemptions for food items purchased through the Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children (WIC) program in California from 2010 to 2018. The data is broken down by vendor (store or other entity where WIC food items can be purchased), county, and year. The table also includes the number of families participating in the WIC program in each county during each year.

The

2019-2020-part-b-wic-redemptions-by-vend.Description:
The table '2019-2020-part-b-wic-redemptions-by-vendor-county-with-family-counts' contains data on the number of redemptions for WIC benefits by vendor and county in California for the period of July 1, 2019 to June 30, 2020. The data also includes the number of families that redeemed benefits at each vendor and county.

The table is organized as follows:

* The first column contains the vendor name.
* The second column contains the county name.
* The third column

Vendor_County_Code.Name: Vendor_County_Code

Vendor_County.Name: Vendor_County
Vendor_County.Description: **Vendor_County :** Name of the county in which the vendor is located.

Number_of_Food_Instruments_Redeemed.Name: Number_of_Food_Instruments_Redeemed

Dollar_Amount_of_EBT_Transactions.Description: **Dollar_Amount_of_EBT_Transactions :** Total dollar value of EBT transactions made at the vendor during the specified month.

Average_Cost_per_Family.Name: Average_Cost_per_Family
Average_Cost_per_Family.Description: **Average_Cost_per_Family :** Calculated as the sum of the dollar amount of food instruments redeemed and the dollar amount of EBT transactions divided by the number of families that redeemed food instruments or used EBT cards at the vendor during the specified month.

Average_Cost_Adjusted.Name: Average_Cost_Adjusted
Average_Cost_Adjusted.Description: **Average_Cost_Adjusted :** Calculated as the Total_Cost_Adjusted divided by the number of families that redeemed food instruments or used EBT cards at the vendor during the specified month.

The data is broken down by county, state, and year, and includes the total number of recipients, the total amount of funds awarded, and the average amount of funds awarded per recipient.

The table can be used to track the distribution of ABCD-350 funds over time and to identify areas that may be underserved. It can also be used to compare the performance of different counties in terms of their ability to attract and retain ABCD-350 funds
